[SN]TITLE[SN]
Eastbourne jewellery raid 'nets up to £100K haul'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Thieves have smashed their way into an Eastbourne jewellery stores and got away with stock worth £50,000 to £100,000.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Sussex Police said the men smashed a window to get into Ernest Jones in the Arndale Centre, just before 13:15 BST.
A member of staff raised the alarm, officers said.
Police want to trace three men who were seen wearing bright ski jackets and scarves covering their faces.
